true","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/8962f6c2075b2cf80ed6daccff85c8a7?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Keri Meredith","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2016-07-22T01:01:05.970-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/1","description":"The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/open.png","name":"Open","id":"1","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10205","id":"10205","name":"User Guide"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"h3. Suspending and Resuming EBS-Backed Instances\r\n\r\n4.2.2: http://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.2/#shared/suspend_resume_instances.html\r\n\r\n4.3.0: http://packages.release.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/origin/master/#shared/suspend_resume_instances.html\r\n\r\nChange to:\r\nh3. Starting, Stopping, and Terminating EBS-Backed Instances\r\n\r\nAnd change the explanations with your wordsmithing...\r\n\r\nSuspending an instance implies that the state of the instance is stopped in time immediately, until it is resumed later. In VMWare, for example, you can suspend an instance, then resume it 5 minutes later. According to the VM itself, nothing has happened except that the time has mysteriously jumped forward by 5 minutes. Processes continue what they were doing.\r\n\r\nNeither AWS nor Eucalyptus does this. Perhaps Eucalyptus did at one time? ([~sjones]?)\r\n\r\nIn the AWS docs page is http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/Stop_Start.html in the Overview section:\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\n\"When you stop a running instance, the following happens:\r\n* The instance performs a normal shutdown and stops running; its status changes to stopping and then stopped.\"\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nhttp://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ec2-instance-lifecycle.html is also helpful FYI.\r\n\r\n{{euca-stop-instances}} actually tells the instance to do a normal operating system shutdown. It doesn't do a suspend. Likewise, {{euca-start-instances}} boots the operating system (as if its power has been off). The {{euca-reboot-instances}} does both in sequence. The {{euca-terminate-instances}} stops it immediately, effectively powering off the instance.\r\n\r\nWe should also say we do NOT support AWS's feature of being able to change the behavior of an instance-initiated shutdown behavior as described in http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/terminating-instances.html#Using_ChangingInstanceInitiatedShutdownBehavior .\r\n","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Change suspend/resume of EBS-Backed Instances to stop/start","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=lincoln.thomas","name":"lincoln.thomas","key":"lincoln.thomas","accountId":"557058:f9364c00-87ee-4948-b657-bb8f8f2030ea","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dlincoln.thomas%26avatarId%3D17800%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/c21bba9797b880c34a5d772e6db4664f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerI